# Project Intake Rules

Apply during **Existing Project Intake** mode (`Current Mode: existing-project-intake`).

## Command Aliases

These user messages **start Existing Project Intake** (case-insensitive):

`Existing Project` · `Existing Project Intake` · `Project Intake` · `Intake` · `Intake this repo` · `Analyze this repo` · `Review this codebase` · `Document this project` · `Existing App`

Treat as **Start Existing Project Intake** with full intake goals, autonomy, and docs-only rules. See `.cursor/workflow/command-aliases.md`.

## Read-Only for App Code

- **Do not modify application source code** during intake
- **Do not install packages** or run destructive commands
- Read, search, and inspect only
- Docs, workflow state, and intake artifacts may be created or updated

## Inspect Before Writing

- **Inspect actual repo files** before writing or updating project-specific docs
- **Do not rely only on user input** — verify claims against code, config, and CI
- Read manifests, entry points, routes, models, tests, CI configs, and existing docs
- Use checklist: `.cursor/workflow/existing-project-intake-checklist.md`

## Tagging Conventions

| Tag | Use when |
|-----|----------|
| `[INFERRED]` | Reasonable conclusion from code/docs; not confirmed by human |
| `[NEEDS HUMAN INPUT]` | Cannot determine safely; requires user decision |
| `[TBD]` | Not yet investigated |
| `[ASSUMED]` | Bootstrap only — not used for established repo facts |

## Required Intake Artifacts

Create or update during intake:

**Plan & signoff:**
- `docs/plans/project-intake-plan.md` — **first**, before other doc work
- `docs/reviews/project-intake-signoff.md` — at completion

**Project docs:**
- `PROJECT_BRIEF.md`, `ARCHITECTURE.md`, `DATA_MODEL.md`, `BACKEND.md`
- `STYLE_GUIDE.md`, `ROADMAP.md`, `TESTING.md`, `DEPLOYMENT.md`
- `DECISIONS.md`, `RISK_REGISTER.md`

**Intake-specific:**
- `PROJECT_HEALTH.md` — health summary and recommended phases
- `INTAKE_FINDINGS.md` — inspection record
- `TECH_DEBT.md` — discovered debt items

Use templates in `.cursor/workflow/project-health-template.md` and `.cursor/workflow/tech-debt-template.md`.

## Identify Issues, Do Not Fix

During intake, identify and document (do **not** implement fixes for):

- Architecture issues (layer violations, coupling)
- Doc vs code mismatches
- Security concerns
- Testing gaps
- Dependency concerns (outdated, vulnerable, unused)
- Accessibility concerns when UI exists
- Deployment gaps

Record fixes as **recommended managed phases** on `ROADMAP.md` and items in `TECH_DEBT.md`.

## Recommend Cleanup, Never Implement During Intake

- Recommend cleanup phases with priority on `PROJECT_HEALTH.md` and `ROADMAP.md`
- **Do not implement cleanup** until user starts an approved Managed Phase

